an class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> agree to a ceretain extent, but some things about their class Vernat was creative about... the grasping roots way of snaring, animal fearing, etc.  And as masters of nature, you'd expect them to call forth the power of nature to do damage, rains, stinging swarms, etc.  But yeah, they get a little bit of everyone elses stuff.... I heard somewhere that they're gonna get breeze at lvl 34 and clarity at lvl 51, LOL, could you imagine!? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 5:26:28 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> I have always believed that Verant went WAY overboard in the development of classes.  Yes, the druid class should have never existed and the ranger class should have simply been given better druid abilities as they proceed through levels.  It is this idea that &quot;more playable classes means better game&quot; that the problems manifests itself.  It is a situation where class balance would not have been NEARLY an issue if we simply cut the number of classes in half and destribute the remaining skills.  But alas, its a bit late now.  I have gone through my vision of the 6 class EQ on other threads so I won't bore you again.  But the logic is sound.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p>http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/NEW4.gif</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uadoryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adoryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 12:25:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> Well I wouldn't go taking ALL that away from them, but they really do seem like a combination of every class. Verant calls them balanced, but I've always thought that they were the most UNbalanced class because they simply have too much. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uflambe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flambe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 4:04:25 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/68/1743268.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> mmm druids.. Well from a guildy, I've heard they get some mana regen for Form of the Howler (2 pts mana regen) and Spirit of Oak (5 pts mana regen), and they both stack with Clarity :P<br>
<br>
