Caramo tells you, "Of those, 15 being lawful citizens, and 157 were justifiable by law."<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulenadaynastardew.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenadayna Stardew</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 8:23:40 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=c:\windows\desktop\lena.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1>    I despise druids.  In fact, I'm thinking of making part of my price for teleporting people sacrificing a Halfling Druid to Innoruuk or Solusek Ro.<br>
<br>
   What other class is practically crying out &quot;NERF ME PLEASE!&quot; and still gets upgrades in every patch?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uoglzogl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>oglzogl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 4:39:47 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.toddpowelson.com/selfish.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> Anybody ever notice how much wisdom casters spells and abilities seem to overlap but when the INT caster asks for something that another class is capable of doing, VI shouts &quot;FOUL&quot; and &quot;that is another classes territory&quot;.<br>
I dont know what it means... maybe nothing. It just cracks me up and I dont understand the logic. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 5:42:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> I know GZ is said to have made the spell system for all the casters, but there is a distinct difference between WIS and INT casters.  Not in feel but in design, WIS and INT casters use precisely the same system (mana breakdown, even mana items are interchangable, fizzles, rules, etc).  But the way they are designed for spells, ability, flexibility, number of spells, etc is just... better.  That was a minor grudge in the past for me, especially when you consider that after level 24 your spells come every 5 levels too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 7:33:24 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> I won't lie, I enjoy playing a druid very very much.  Simply from a standpoint of certain things...<br>
<br>
1. Variety - A nice balance of heals, buffs, nukes, DoT, etc<br>
2. Usefulness - In the later druid game, they are quite a nice addition from a resistance standpoint (the Circle spells); And they are being tweaked more and more in the healing department.<br>
3. Certain &quot;Fun&quot; spell additions - I love wolf form, and I love the bear pet, regardless of how limited the use is.  They are simply FUN!<br>
<br>
<br>
Yes, I have a deep resentment because of the well rounded aspects (sort of melting pot) that druids have been given.  They DO seem to be a trickle down of all the classes.  You could argue the same to a degree about us.  BUT...<br>
<br>
Wizard - combining snares, stuns, bad damage shields, and ports with heavy nukes<br>
<br>
or<br>
<br>
Druids - combining snares, stuns, ports, medium heavy nukes(later), above average heals(later), very good buffs, SoW, excellent damage shields, etc.<br>
<br>
There is simply so much more to play with.  There is no one single way to play them.  And THAT is majorly why I don't like them.  I love my wizard.  I simply wish we had more things to play with.  lol.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucryndarkfire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cryn Darkfire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif  BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 7:49:54 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/equipment/fashion/bonecaster_human_female.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> Druids - combining snares, stuns, ports, medium heavy nukes(later), above average heals(later), very good buffs, SoW, excellent damage shields, etc.<br>
<br>
Don't FORGET Tracking!<br>
<br>
