Cazic-Thule shouts "YOU SHALL NOT EVADE ME CRYN!" <BR> <BR>
YOU HAVE BEEN SLAIN BY CAZIC-THULE! <BR>
Loading please wait...
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umarktodd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MarkTodd</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 10:18:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> I remember reading something said by one of the creators of EQ regarding their use of the class system versus a skill system. Something to the effect that they didn't want users to be able to create these homogenous characters that could do it all. Therefore we have the class system with limited class abilities that encourage grouping. <br>
<br>
But then they created the druid that can do a bit of everything. Naturally people flock to the class. And now with all the druids running around it would seem to me that we have the situation Verant wanted to avoid. But instead of the users creating the do-it-all characters, Verant did it. <p>Merkus Stormcrow (40, High Elf, Mostly Retired Wizard)
<BR>
Knorm Knimbleknife
(21, Dwarf, Rogue)
<BR>
Rukus (6, Half-elven, Bongo Banging Bard)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usilvius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 4:57:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> Ya know, the do it all system isn't so bad. The Realm from Sierra, while not the greatest of games was still fun. Had the Do-it-all system. The way it worked was Fighters took more skill points to learn magic, and magic users took more skill points to learn fighting, other classes took a medium, and race effected how good you were. Ogres hit harder, elves have less chance of fizzles. To top it, all mana was controlled by purchasable crystalls so having 1-2million was not uncommon. All-in-all the game was fairly fun, and struggling for groups was not a problem. For highlevel mobs you summoned monsters to protect you, went invis, and whacked at the mob while summoning more monsters to proctect you. There was no ranting, no screaming over what class is over powered, sometimes simple is better, and uncreative can lend to the creative.<br>
<br>
Silvius Wayfarer<br>
44th Wizard of Drinal (EQ)<br>
Healingwind<br>
200th Wizard of The Realm (Sierra) (Ret)<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 6:07:40 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/NEW4.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> I feel the same way about Asherons Call.  Yes, it doesn't have the flavor that EQ has.  But the exp system, the ability to make money, the class system being one of personal creativity and not rigid casts, it is all much more well rounded.  The druid class is actually much more like those classes than the rest of EQ.  Renaissance men and women.  They excel at an enormous amount of skills.  I simply wish for that kind of variety or effectiveness.  Not that wizards aren't effective.  Of course they are.  Just a bit low on the dimentions. <p><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith.gif" border="0"><BR><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith2.gif" border="0"><BR><img src="http://wraithwave.homestead.com/files/Wraith3.gif" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udarret.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darret</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/15/01 10:57:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids</span><hr size=1> I dont hate druids, I just dispise all that they were givein, true on Fennin Ro druid have about the same group ability as wizards (slim to none)(talking about 50+ here).<br>
<br>
While I'm fairly good at quading just once I would like to harmony pull an 8k hp mob (sentients in WL) root it, stack 4 dots on it, then sit and med.<br>
<br>
Some might flame me and say I have &quot;druid envy&quot; but there is no way I would ever EVER switch to some hairy footed halfling druid.<br>
<br>
<br>
Darret 57 Wizard<br>
Dragonriders of Norrath, Fennin Ro <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udarret.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darret</A> at: 7/16/01 12:16:32 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=236.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=332.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=204.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.threadControl?topicID=204.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=204.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=204.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class